      "source": [
        "# Trajectory Distribution Fuzzing in Highway Roundabout\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook demonstrates trajectory distribution fuzzing for the HighwayEnv roundabout environment.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Key Components** (now in `src/` modules):\n",
        "- `ScenarioParams`: Dataclass for configurable observation, action, and environment disturbances\n",
        "- `SimulatedEnv`: Custom roundabout environment with fuzzable parameters\n",
        "- `ScenarioFuzzer`: Class for rollouts and finding critical failure scenarios\n",
        "\n",
        "**Usage**: Create a `ScenarioFuzzer` with env and model, then call:\n",
        "- `fuzzer.rollout()` for individual trajectory sampling\n",
        "- `fuzzer.optimize()` for L-BFGS falsification (find most likely failures)\n",
        "- `fuzzer.mcmc_sample()` for MCMC sampling from the failure distribution"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "eaa170e4",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Uncomment to install dependencies\n",
        "# !pip install gymnasium stable_baselines3 opencv-python highway_env torch"
      ]
    },
