    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "5b6644fb",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## MCMC Failure Distribution Sampling\n",
        "\n",
        "Use Metropolis-Hastings MCMC to sample from a distribution that overweights failure-prone parameter configurations. This provides a more complete picture of the failure landscape than gradient-based optimization alone.\n",
        "\n",
        "The target distribution is: π(θ) ∝ p(θ) · [1 + w · P(failure|θ)]\n",
        "\n",
        "where w is a failure weight that controls how much we oversample failures."
      ]
    },
